  "prompt": "What is a normal waist size for a women?",
  "response": "Waist size can vary widely among individuals due to different body types, heights, and genetic factors. However, general guidelines can provide an average range for women's waist sizes.\n\nAccording to various health organizations and studies:\n- A healthy waist circumference for women is typically considered to be less than 35 inches (88 centimeters). This is because excessive abdominal fat can increase the risk of health conditions such as heart disease, diabetes, and certain cancers.\n- The average waist size for adult women in the United States is around 38 to 40 inches.\n\nIt's important to remember that these are general guidelines and averages; individual healthy waist sizes can differ. Factors such as muscle tone, body composition, and overall health should be considered rather than focusing solely on measurements. Consulting with healthcare professionals for personalized health assessments is always recommended.",
